# 03 – Divergence Analysis

This file documents **where and why** the six AI models disagree. Divergence is not treated as an error but as the central epistemic resource of the Triangulation nach Schult (TNS) method.

Only **substantive** (factual/causal) and **normative** (value‑based) divergences influence the final synthesis. Didactic and architectural differences are noted but not weighted.

